nd-on-way-to-maha-kumbh-7593648%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia's%20having%20problems%20with%20its%20newest%20ICBM.%20It%20drove%20away%20critical%20Ukrainian%20missile%20expertise.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20Sarmat%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missil%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63f62f5e88f76900192cd176%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22822%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussia's%20Sarmat%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%20is%20launched%20in%20Russia's%20northwest%20region%20of%20Plesetsk%20in%20April%202022.%3Cp%3ERoscosmos%20Space%20Agency%20Press%20Service%20via%20AP%2C%20File%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERussia%20is%20experiencing%20repeated%20struggles%20with%20its%20new%20ICBM.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERussia%20used%20to%20use%20Ukrainian%20expertise%20to%20work%20on%20that%20type%20of%20missile.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20Russia's%20attack%20on%20Ukraine%20in%202014%20and%20its%202022%20invasion%20isolated%20it%20from%20that%20expertise.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-icbm-test-fail-hints-at-new-missile-problems-analysts-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EICBM%20program%20is%20in%20trouble%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20facing%20persistent%20struggles%20with%20its%20new%20Sarmat%20missile.%20And%20it%20doesn't%20help%20that%20it's%20cut%20off%20expertise%20it%20once%20depended%20on%20by%20waging%20war%20on%20its%20neighbor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHistorically%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20ICBM%20manufacturing%20plants%20and%20personnel%20were%20based%20in%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20Timothy%20Wright%2C%20a%20missile%20expert%20at%20the%20International%20Institute%20for%20Strategic%20Studies%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221112a4db-706a-4e4d-a449-ee8881ff4e66%5C%22%3EUkrainian%20expertise%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20became%20independent%20when%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20collapsed%20in%201991%2C%20but%20its%20defense%20industry%20continued%20to%20be%20intertwined%20with%20Russia.%20Ukraine%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieendowment.org%2Fresearch%2F2014%2F07%2Fsaving-ukraines-defense-industry%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpertise%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20nuclear%20and%20missile%20technology%2C%20as%20well%20as%20manufacturing%20knowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20had%20been%20decreasing%20its%20reliance%20but%20had%20not%20yet%20severed%20critical%20ties%20when%20it%20attacked%20Ukraine%20in%202014%2C%20leaving%20it%20with%20gaps%20that%20could%20affect%20development%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20Russia%20has%20developed%20capable%20solid-fueled%20ICBMs.%20But%20with%20Sarmat%2C%20it%20decided%20to%20use%20a%20liquid-fueled%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20with%20that%20%26quot%3Bis%20that%20the%20Russians%20haven't%20done%20this%20in%20about%2030-plus%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20explained.%20%26quot%3BThey%20haven't%20got%20any%20recent%20experience%20doing%20this%20sort%20of%20stuff%20with%20land-based%20ICBMs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFabian%20Hoffman%2C%20a%20missile%20expert%20at%20the%20Oslo%20Nuclear%20Project%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20it's%20%26quot%3Ba%20bit%20of%20a%20question%20of%3A%20'Have%20they%20retained%20the%20expertise%3F'%20Because%20all%20the%20people%20who%20built%20their%20previous%20missile%20have%20retired%20or%20dead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20them%20are%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20had%20a%20big%20part%20in%20the%20Russian%20ICBM%20program%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20that's%20a%20major%20issue.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWright%20described%20Russia's%20choice%20to%20use%20liquid%20fuel%20technology%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20really%20weird%20choice%20that%20they%20made%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20%26quot%3Bis%20something%20the%20Ukrainians%20previously%20did%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20%26quot%3Bthat's%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20why%20they're%20having%20lots%20of%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20fish-eye%20image%20shows%20a%20missile%20launching%20above%20a%20snowy%20ground%20with%20a%20blue%20and%20cloudy%20sky%20behind%20it.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6797683aeb4be2fff9a23073%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221118%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Sarmat%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%20is%20launched%20from%20Plesetsk%20in%20northwestern%20Russia%20in%20April%202022.%3Cp%3ERussian%20Defense%20Ministry%20Press%20Service%20via%20AP%2C%20File%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Sarmat%20is%20designed%20to%20replace%20the%20Soviet-era%20R-36%2C%20which%20NATO%20calls%20the%20SS-18%20%26quot%3BSatan.%26quot%3B%20Its%20earliest%20version%20first%20entered%20service%20in%20the%201970s%20and%20has%20been%20modified%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20that%20designed%20and%20maintained%20it%2C%20Pivdenmash%2C%20known%20as%20Yuzhmash%20in%20Russia%2C%20was%20in%20what%20is%20now%20modern-day%20Ukraine.%20(Russia%20appeared%20to%20target%20the%20Pivdenmash%20plant%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-oreshnik-what-know-about-experimental-missile-used-against-ukraine-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20attack%20with%20a%20new%20missile%20type%20in%20November%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223cc5ca57-c645-4a22-970f-cde2d190dceb%5C%22%3EUkraine%20cut%20ties%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20wanted%20to%20develop%20more%20of%20this%20kind%20of%20expertise%20and%20capability%20itself.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20Russia%20found%20itself%20in%20a%20position%20where%20essentially%20it%20was%20having%20to%20rely%20on%20exte