%20is%20the%20crown%20jewel%20of%20the%20Queen%20of%20Hills%2C%20famous%20with%20anyone%20and%20everyone%20who%20has%20been%20to%20Darjeeling.%20The%20Elgin%20has%20been%20around%20for%20over%20a%20century.%20It%20is%20the%20most%20famous%20landmark%20in%20Darjeeling%2C%20and%20was%20once%20the%20summer%20home%20of%20the%20Maharaja%20of%20Cooch%20Behar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201887%2C%20Maharaja%20Nripendra%20Narayan%20of%20Cooch%20Behar%20built%20the%20place%20as%20a%20manor%20house%2C%20to%20serve%20as%20his%20summer%20residence.%20The%20Cooch%20Behars%20spent%20many%20summers%20in%20Darjeeling%2C%20a%20hill%20station%20200%20kilometres%20from%20their%20capital%20in%20the%20foothills%20of%20the%20Himalayas%2C%20where%20April-May-June%20meant%20temperatures%20in%20the%2030-something-Celsius%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Elgin%20was%20built%20as%20a%20manor%20house%20for%20the%20Maharaja%20of%20Cooch%20Behar%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20Elgin%20was%20built%20as%20a%20manor%20house%20for%20the%20Maharaja%20of%20Cooch%20Behar%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2F199hpipg_the-elgin-was-built-as-a-manor-house-for-the-maharaja-of-cooch-behar_625x300_30_January_25.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Elgin%20was%20built%20as%20a%20manor%20house%20for%20the%20Maharaja%20of%20Cooch%20Behar%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Nripendra%20Narayan's%20death%20in%201911%2C%20the%20property%20passed%20on%20to%20his%20son%20and%20successor%2C%20Rajendra%20Narayan%20II.%20Later%2C%20it%20was%20leased%20to%20British%20families%20like%20the%20Pavions%20and%20Oakleys.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201965%2C%20Kuldip%20Chand%20Oberoi%20-%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fortuneindia.com%2Fpeople%2Fthe-hotel-industrys-other-oberoi%2F100521%5C%22%3Ethe%20'other%20Oberoi'%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Oberoi%20family%20of%20hoteliers%20-%20got%20his%20lifetime%20savings%20of%20Rs%203%20lakh%20out%20and%20bought%20the%20place%20from%20Nancy%20Oakley%2C%20who%20it%20had%20been%20leased%20to.%20Oakley%20was%20running%20the%20place%20as%20a%20guest%20house%20that%20Oberoi%20had%20rented.%20Oberoi%20bought%20The%20Elgin.%20Three%20years%20later%2C%20when%20Oakley%20left%20India%20for%20England%2C%20Kuldip%20Chand%20Oberoi%20established%20and%20registered%20a%20firm%20called%20%26quot%3BNew%20Elgin%20Hotel%26quot%3B%2C%20with%20himself%20as%20the%20sole%20proprietor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201975%2C%20the%20firm%20became%20a%20partnership%20firm%2C%20and%20subsequently%2C%20in%201995%2C%20transitioned%20into%20a%20private%20limited%20company.%20Brij%20Raj%20Oberoi%2C%20Kuldip's%20son%2C%20joined%20his%20father%20in%20assisting%20with%20the%20upkeep%20of%20The%20Elgin%20when%20he%20was%20only%2020%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20the%20Elgin%20has%20undergone%20extensive%20refurbishment%20and%20restoration%2C%20and%20the%20Oberois%20have%20ensured%20that%20they%20retain%20the%20glory%20of%20the%20original%20manor%20house%20that%20the%20Maharaja%20of%20Cooch%20Behar%20had%20envisioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20autumn%20of%201976%2C%20Wangchuk%20Tenzing%20Namgyal%2C%20the%20Crown%20Prince%20of%20Sikkim%2C%20was%20at%20The%20Elgin%20after%20a%20football%20match%20against%20the%20local%20team.%20Sikkim%20won%20that%20match%203-1.%20When%20Brij%20Raj%20invited%20Namgyal%20for%20a%20drink%20at%20the%20hotel%20that%20evening%2C%20they%20got%20to%20talking%20about%20the%20place.%20The%20hotelier%20shared%20his%20plans%20of%20%26quot%3Bmodernising%26quot%3B%20the%20manor%20house.%20Namgyal%20was%20aghast.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo!%20Never%20do%20that.%20It%20has%20taken%20decades%20to%20build%20this%20atmosphere%20-%20it's%20so%20personal!%20Nothing%20can%20substitute%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOberoi%20took%20Namgyal's%20advice%20in%20his%20stride%20and%20left%20Elgin%20the%20way%20it%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20corridors%20of%20The%20Elgin%20are%20lined%20with%20frames%20of%20its%20famed%20guests%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20corridors%20of%20The%20Elgin%20are%20lined%20with%20frames%20of%20its%20famed%20guests%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fe8uoffbg_elgin-corridors_625x300_30_January_25.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20corridors%20of%20The%20Elgin%20are%20lined%20with%20frames%20of%20its%20famed%20guests%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20stepping%20into%20The%20Elgin%20is%20stepping%20into%20a%20bygone%20era.%20You'll%20find%20period%20Burma%20teak%20furniture%2C%20fireplaces%20from%20the%201800s%2C%20lithographs%20by%20William%20Daniell.%20You'll%20also%20find%20framed%20photographs%20of%20the%20who's%20who%20who%20have%20visited%20The%20Elgin%20-%20and%20quite%20a%20list%20that%20is!%20From%20the%20Crown%20Prince%20of%20Sikkim%2C%20to%20French%20author%20Dominique%20Lapierre%2C%20and%20British%20journalist-author%20Mark%20Tully%2C%20the%20hotel%20was%20the%20only%20residence%20of%20choice%20in%20Darjeeling%20for%20guests%20for%20many%20decades.%20Add%20to%20that%20all%20the%20film%20stars%20who%20spent%20their%20holidays%20in%20Darjeeling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20place%20crowded%20with%20hotels%2C%20what%20is%20that%20attracts%20guests%20to%20The%20Elgin%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20the%20word's%20heritage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Oberois%20kept%20old-world%20charm%20in%20mind%20while%20doing%20up%20their%20portfolio%20of%20hotels%20in%20North%20Bengal%20and%20Sikkim.%20Their%20hotels%20score%20big%20on%20heritage.%20Nostalgia%20is%20a%20money-spinner%2C%20and%20the%20Oberois%20know%20it%20all%20too%20well.%20So%2C%20while%20the%20Elgins%20are%20now%20'modernised'%20with%20all%20amenities%20that%20you%20need%2C%20there's%20still%20the%20awe%20of%20having%20crossed%20over%20to%20a%20different%20era%2C%20feet%20firm%20in%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Elgin%20group%20has%20enjoyed%20a%20largely%20unrivalled%20few%20decades%20in%20North%20Bengal%20and%20Sikkim%2C%20primarily%20because%20of%20just%20how%20politically%20volatile%20the%20area%20has%20been.%20All%20through%20the%20turbulent%202000s%2C%20Darjeeling%20has%20seen%20turmoil.%20Gorkhaland%20is%20a%20simmering%20issue%20that%20is%20only%20papered%20over%20by%20the%20West%20Bengal%20government.%20There%20are%20talks%20and%20elections%2C%20but%20the%20reality%20on%20the%20ground%20is%20still%20tense.%20Tourists%20here%20have%20mostly%20been%20from%20West%20Bengal%2C%20although%20things%20are%20evolving%20fast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Jaideep%20Ahlawat%20in%20a%20still%20from%20Paatal%20Lok%202.%20Screenshot%3A%20Amazon%20Prime%20Video%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Jaideep%20Ahlawat%20in%20a%20still%20from%20Paatal%20Lok%202.%20Screenshot%3A%20Amazon%20Prime%20Video%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fgp3a1jno_elgin-darjeeling-in-paatal-lok-2_625x300_30_January_25.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJaideep%20Ahlawat%20in%20a%20still%20from%20Paatal%20Lok%202.%20Screenshot%3A%20Amazon%20Prime%20Video%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20the%20bigger%20groups%20of%20hotels%20like%20the%20Taj%2C%20the%20Leela%2C%20and%20the%20EIH%20(East%20India%20Hotels)%20that%20own%20the%20Oberoi%20hotels%2C%20decided%20to%20stay%20away.%20It%20is%20only%20in%20December%202020%20that%20Taj%20first%20arrived%20in%20Darjeeling%2C%20with%20Chia%20Kutir.%20The%20Oberois%20had%20Mount%20Everest%20in%20Darjeeling%20in%20the%2050s%2C%20but%20a%20fire%20in%20the%2070s%20swallowed%20the%20building.%20The%20hotel%20never%20reopened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20for%20The%20Elgin%20to%20bet%20on%20the%20area%20was%20also%20a%20gamble%20that%20paid%20off%2C%20one%20would%20say.%20Bollywood%20has%20been%20a%20fairweather%20friend%20with%20visits%20every%20now%20and%20then.%20Since%20