older-grandparent-perfect-time-having-kids-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewaiting%20longer%20to%20have%20children%3C%2Fa%3E.%20According%20to%20the%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%2C%20the%20average%20age%20at%20which%20a%20woman%20first%20gives%20birth%20is%20about%2027.%20It's%20not%20so%20much%20that%20women%20are%20choosing%20their%20careers%20over%20having%20children%2C%20but%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-expensive-cities-for-childcare-daycare-us-affordable-care-cost-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20of%20raising%20a%20child%3C%2Fa%3E%20skyrockets%2C%20more%20feel%20like%20they%20need%20to%20wait%20until%20their%20careers%20are%20established%20to%20start%20a%20family.%20The%20trouble%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-paying-fast-growing-jobs-software-developers-nurses-managers-accountants-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-paying%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20often%20the%20most%20demanding%2C%20and%20many%20people's%20careers%20start%20taking%20off%20in%20their%2030s%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20time%20many%20feel%20ready%20to%20have%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20talked%20to%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20mothers%20working%20in%20fields%20such%20as%20finance%2C%20retail%2C%20and%20consulting%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20referred%20to%20by%20just%20their%20first%20name%20to%20avoid%20professional%20repercussions.%20Most%20of%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelayed-having-kids-financial-reasons-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewaited%20to%20have%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%20until%20they%20felt%20secure%20and%20financially%20stable%20enough%20in%20their%20careers%20to%20do%20so%2C%20only%20to%20find%20it%20difficult%20to%20juggle%20motherhood%20with%20increasing%20career%20pressures.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20they%20say%2C%20their%20employers%20did%20little%20to%20accommodate%20them%2C%20underscoring%20a%20simple%20truth%3A%20For%20many%20mothers%2C%20work%20is%20not%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Anastasia%20Dedik%2C%20a%2043-year-old%20professional%20musician%20who%20came%20to%20the%20US%20from%20Russia%2C%20starting%20a%20family%20wasn't%20even%20a%20consideration%20until%20she%20finished%20her%20education%20and%20established%20herself%20professionally.%20By%20that%20time%2C%20she%20was%2032.%20Two%20and%20a%20half%20weeks%20after%20she%20had%20her%20daughter%2C%20she%20was%20back%20at%20work%20as%20a%20piano%20teacher%20and%20performer.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20wanted%20to%20make%20sure%20I%20still%20had%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Still%2C%20it%20was%20tough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20my%20daughter%20was%203%20weeks%20old%2C%20I%20had%20to%20go%20to%20California%20for%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20the%20end%20of%20breastfeeding.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20mothers%20I%20talked%20to%20shared%20similar%20stories%20about%20wanting%20to%20ensure%20career%20stability%20before%20having%20a%20baby%3B%20many%20say%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-daycare-cost-new-york-city-crisis-housing-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20of%20childcare%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20a%20big%20reason%20they%20waited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20felt%20irresponsible%20to%20even%20start%20thinking%20about%20having%20a%20baby%20at%20a%20time%20when%20I%20was%20spending%20a%20lot%20of%20my%20life%20worrying%20about%20paying%20rent%20and%20paying%20off%20college%20debt%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Molly%2C%20a%20mother%20of%20one%20in%20New%20York%20City%20who%20works%20in%20publishing.%20She%20had%20her%20daughter%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20she%20was%2038.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20calculated%20that%20paying%20for%20day%20care%20or%20a%20nanny%20would%20leave%20her%20and%20her%20husband%20%E2%80%94%20who%20works%20in%20tech%20%E2%80%94%20with%20little%20to%20no%20savings%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202023%20survey%20conducted%20by%20the%20American%20Psychological%20Association%2C%2066%25%20of%20parents%20reported%20feeling%20%26quot%3Bconsumed%26quot%3B%20by%20worries%20about%20money%2C%20compared%20with%2039%25%20of%20adults%20who%20weren't%20parents.%20A%20Pew%20survey%20from%202024%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20found%20that%20among%20adults%20under%2050%20who%20didn't%20have%20children%2C%2036%25%20said%20a%20major%20reason%20was%20that%20they%20didn't%20think%20they%20could%20afford%20to%20raise%20a%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20women%20I%20talked%20to%20who%20waited%20until%20their%2030s%20to%20have%20children%20largely%20said%20they%20were%20confident%20they%20made%20the%20right%20decision%2C%20many%20women%20also%20described%20feeling%20like%20the%20choices%20they%20made%20weren't%20really%20choices%20%E2%80%94%20they%20were%20forced%20into%20the%20decision%20because%20no%20other%20option%20made%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20wasn't%20ready%20to%20start%20a%20family%20earlier%2C%26quot%3B%20June%2C%20a%20consultant%20living%20in%20London%20who%20had%20her%20first%20child%20at%2036%2C%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BI%20felt%20insecure%20in%20my%20work%2C%20didn't%20have%20significant%20savings%2C%20and%20wanted%20to%20spend%20some%20time%20living%20with%20my%20partner%20before%20really%20deciding%20that%20we%20want%20kids.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20and%20her%20partner%20also%20wanted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdinks-buy-homes-parents-spend-most-income-on-mortgage-childcare-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuy%20a%20house%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20adding%20on%20the%20cost%20of%20children.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20can't%20rush%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20They%20ended%20up%20buying%20the%20house%20and%20moving%20in%20when%20she%20was%20a%20few%20months%20pregnant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20the%20women%20said%20they%20felt%20financially%20secure%2C%20their%20careers%20had%20also%20ramped%20up.%20Many%20said%20that%20after%20having%20a%20baby%20they%20tried%20to%20return%20to%20work%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%20fearful%20that%20%E2%80%94%20despite%20widespread%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffired-pregnant-maternity-leave-employment-lawyer-advice-workplace-discrimination-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epregnancy%20antidiscrimination%3C%2Fa%3E%20laws%20%E2%80%94%20they'd%20be%20passed%20over%20for%20promotions%20and%20pay%20raises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20me%2C%20it%20was%20a%20fear%20of%20becoming%20irrelevant%20if%20I%20stayed%20away%20too%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Anita%2C%20a%2039-year-old%20marketing%20executive%20and%20mother%20of%20two%20who%20lives%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20New%20York.%20She%20was%20particularly%20afraid%20that%20her%20relationships%20with%20clients%20would%20deteriorate%20while%20she%20was%20away.%20%26quot%3BI%20felt%20like%20this%20would%20set%20me%20back%20on%20my%20career%20trajectory%2C%20that%20it%20would%20cause%20me%20to%20lose%20respectability%20and%20influence%20within%20the%20industry%20and%20therefore%20become%20less%20valuable%20to%20my%20employer.%26quot%3B%20That%2C%20she%20says%2C%20is%20what%20kept%20her%20from%20starting%20a%20family%20in%20her%2020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20her%20first%20kid%20at%2033.%20The%20timing%20gave%20her%20more%20financial%20stability%20and%20confidence%20in%20her%20career%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-work-after-maternity-leave-google-ai-engineer-tech-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturning%20from%20her%20three-month%20maternity%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20far%20from%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20sacrifice%20I%20had%20to%20make%20almost%20immediately%20was%20nursing%20my%20baby%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20recalls.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20really%20hard%20to%20nurse%20or%20express%20milk%20when%20I%20was%20going%20back%20into%20the%20office%2C%20so%20we%20switched%20to%20formula.%20It%20broke%20my%20heart%20that%20this%20was%20a%20decision%20I%20was%20making%20explicitly%20because%20of%20my%20work%20requirements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20women%20than%20ever%20before%20hold%20what%20the%20Harvard%20economic%20historian%20and%20labor%20economist%20Claudia%20Goldin%20calls%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2021%2F09%2Fthe-problem-with-greedy-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bgreedy%26quot%3B%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20roles%20that%20promise%20prestige%2C%20seniority%2C%20and%20a%20generous%20salary%20but%20that%20also%20require%20a%20lot%20of%20hours%20at%20unpredictable%20times%20of%20the%20day.%20Pursuing%20these%20jobs%20can%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20a%20family%2C%20but%20balancing%20them%20with%20motherhood%20is%20often%20impossible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20actually%20contacted%20by%20a%20recruiter%20while%20I%20was%20on%20maternity%20leave%2C%26quot%3B%20Anita%20says.%20The%20job%20%26quot%3Bwas%20more%20prestigious%20and%20better%20paid%2C%20but%20it%20would've%20involved%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20travel%2C%20so%20I%20didn't%20even%20apply.%26quot%3B%20Other%20women%20said%20that%20after%20having%20children%20they%20felt%20forced%20to%20forgo%20certain%20professional%20opportunities%2C%20such%20as%20taking%20on%20high-profile%20projects%20or%20pursuing%20new%20roles%2C%20because%20of%20their%20caring%20responsibilities.%20In%20a%20Gallup%20survey%20last%20year%2C%2059%25%20of%20women%20said%20they%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareerist-corporate-ladder-decline-promotions-work-ethic-american-dream-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturn%20down%20a%20promotion%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20required%20them%20to%20work%2060%20hours%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20a%20greater%20share%20than%20the%20men%20who%20said%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20of%20us%20can't%20just%20opt%20out%20of%20parenting%20when%20it's%20inconvenient%20%E2%80%94%20when%20it%20might%20force%20us%20to%20miss%20a%20work%20deadline%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Nadia%2C%20a%2037-year-old%20consultant%20and%20mother%20of%20two%20from%20Canada.%20Parenting%20is%20a%20full-time%20job%2C%20she%20adds%2C%20even%20if%20you%20have%20another%20full-time%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.library.hbs.edu%2Fworking-knowledge%2Fresearchers-prove-c-suite-gender-gap-but-can-t-explain-it%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20study%20conducted%20in%20Sweden%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20decade%20ago%20found%20that%20female%20executives%20were%20less%20likely%20than%20their%20male%20counterparts%20to%20be%20married%2C%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20divorced%2C%20and%2C%20on%20average%2C%20had%20fewer%20children.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20surprising%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadia%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20evidence%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20women%20simply%20can't%20have%20it%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnita%20blames%20social%20norms.%20%26quot%3BWho%20does%20the%20day%20care%20call%20when%20a%20child%20gets%20sick%3F%20Mom.%20Who%20tends%20to%20deal%20with%20all%20of%20the%20admin%20associated%20with%20kids%3F%20Mom.%20Of%20course%2C%20there%20are%20exceptions%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20in%20so%20many%20heterosexual%20couples%2C%20if%20no%20explicit%20effort%20is%20made%20to%20redress%20the%20balance%20of%20responsibilities%2C%20Mom%20is%20still%20the%20primary%20parent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20employers%20could%20do%20to%20even%20the%20scales.%20Some%20mothers%20told%20me%20that%20their%20requests%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-hybrid-jobs-rto-jpmorgan-amazon-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20remotely%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20largely%20denied%20apart%20from%20emergency%20situations.%20Others%20said%20they%20were%20made%20to%20feel%20guilty%20for%20having%20to%20take%20time%20out%20to%20pump%20breast%20milk%20or%20leave%20work%20at%20a%20set%20time%20to%20accommodate%20childcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20more%20companies%20are%20offering%20benefits%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffertility-benefits-a-must-for-attracting-millennial-talent-ceo-says-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaying%20for%20fertility%20treatments%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20several%20women%20argued%20that%20employers%20should%20first%20focus%20on%20creating%20work%20environments%20that%20truly%20accommodate%20pregnancy%20and%20parenthood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20certain%20irony%20to%20an%20employer%20helping%20someone%20get%20pregnant%20but%20then%20not%20providing%20the%20support%20she%20needed%20once%20the%20baby's%20been%20born%2C%26quot%3B%20Anita%20says.%20For%20instance%2C%20many%20companies%20don't%20offer%20things%20like%20generous%20parental%20leave%2C%20accommodations%20for%20returning%20to%20work%2C%20subsidized%20childcare%2C%20and%20facilities%20for%20pumping%20breast%20milk.%20%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20like%20some%20companies%20are%20paying%20lip%20service%20here%20but%20not%20really%20putting%20themselves%20in%20parents'%20shoes%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJune%2C%20the%20consultant%20in%20London%2C%20says%20she'd%20like%20to%20see%20her%20bosses%20leading%20by%20example%20more%20by%20taking%20all%20the%20parental%20leave%20they're%20entitled%20to.%20%26quot%3BThat%20also%20includes%20senior%20women%20who%20have%20children%20being%20more%20open%20about%20how%20they've%20navigated%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20sometimes%20feels%20like%20I'm%20completely%20alone%20in%20trying%20to%20figure%20everything%20out%2C%20like%20no%20one%20has%20ever%20done%20this%20before%20me.%20And%20that's%20really%20tough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20that%20high-ranking%20women%20aren't%20taking%20all%20the%20leave%20they're%20entitled%20to%20underscores%20the%20problem%3A%20Even%20women%20in%20power%20feel%20afraid%20of%20falling%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20silver%20lining%20is%20that%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgentle-parenting-bust-millennial-parents-helicopter-kids-misbehave-permissive-authoritative-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillennial%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20going%20in%20a%20different%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLots%20of%20millennials%20now%20%E2%80%94%20both%20men%20and%20women%20%E2%80%94%20say%20that%20they're%20going%20to%20take%20a%20career%20break%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Neha%20Ruch%2C%20a%20mother%20of%20two%20who%20wrote%20%26quot%3BThe%20Power%20Pause%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20book%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-mom-quit-job-sabbatical-fintech-startup-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etaking%20a%20career%20break%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20having%20kids.%20%26quot%3BHiring%20managers%20are%20getting%20used%20to%20that%20and%20are%20increasingly%20saying%20that%20they%20would%20overlook%20a%20career%20break%20if%20it%20was%20strategically%20packaged.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%20added%20%26quot%3BStay%20at%20Home%20Parent%26quot%3B%20as%20an%20option%20in%20its%20drop-down%20menu%20of%20job%20titles.%20In%202022%2C%20it%20added%20a%20%26quot%3BCareer%20Break%26quot%3B%20label.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.staffingindustry.com%2Fnews%2Fglobal-daily-news%2Faustralian-workers-keen-to-experience-the-benefits-of-a-career-break%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20survey%20conducted%20in%20Australia%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202024%20suggested%20that%20employees%20were%20more%20willing%20to%20take%20an%20extended%20career%20break%20than%20they%20were%20before%20the