0reports.%20The%20spokesperson%20added%20that%20a%20full-time%20employee%20with%20one%20or%20more%20direct%20reports%20is%20considered%20a%20manager%20%26quot%3Bin%20title%2C%26quot%3B%20regardless%20of%20the%20number%20of%20direct%20reports%20they%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b8bce195-8286-47cd-b474-423cbc4ae175%5C%22%3EPause%20hiring%20new%20managers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22AWS%20CEO%20Matt%20Garman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67772059e5726ab18d0e5d43%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAWS%20CEO%20Matt%20Garman%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20guidelines%20for%20the%20AWS%20sales%20team%20also%20require%20pausing%20new%20manager%20hires.%20This%20is%20temporary%20until%20the%20team%20understands%20the%20full%20ramifications%20of%20the%20organizational%20change%2C%20the%20guidelines%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20particular%20AWS%20team%20has%20discussed%20hiring%20fewer%20middle%20managers%20since%20at%20least%20April%20of%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20another%20internal%20document%20obtained%20by%20BI.%20The%20team%20found%20that%20the%20hiring%20pace%20of%20middle%20managers%20had%20outpaced%20entry-level%20employees%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20resulting%20in%20increased%20costs.%20The%20document%20recommended%20hiring%20more%20early-career%20professionals%20to%20shift%20the%20team's%20structure%20from%20a%20%26quot%3Bdiamond%26quot%3B-shaped%20organization%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bpyramid%26quot%3B%20shape%20where%20more%20than%20half%20the%20team%20is%20concentrated%20in%20lower-level%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20trend%20is%20happening%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20corporate%20America.%20Besides%20Amazon%2C%20companies%20including%20Meta%2C%20Citi%2C%20and%20UPS%20have%20made%20changes%20to%20trim%20supervisory%20roles.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-manager-hiring-white-collar-recession-layoffs-jobs-efficiency-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EData%20from%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20that%20companies%20are%20cutting%20middle%20managers%20and%20not%20backfilling%20those%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20Amazon%20internal%20guideline%20from%20September%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-fewer-managers-leaked-document-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20obtained%20by%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20the%20manager%20reduction%20plan%20could%20result%20in%20role%20eliminations%20as%20%26quot%3Borganizations%20may%20identify%20roles%20that%20are%20no%20longer%20required.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20note%20published%20last%20week%2C%20Bank%20of%20America%20analysts%20estimated%20that%20Amazon%20could%20save%20roughly%20%241.5%20billion%20in%20annual%20costs%20from%20the%20manager%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon's%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20adjusts%20hiring%20based%20on%20business%20needs%2C%20and%20it%20continues%20to%20have%20open%20manager%20roles%20available.%20The%20spokesperson%20added%20that%20there%20are%20many%20ways%20to%20reduce%20the%20number%20of%20managers%20without%20terminating%20them%2C%20such%20as%20by%20reconfiguring%20teams%20or%20reassigning%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22873d0829-cec0-4e9d-90c7-131087c5817c%5C%22%3EDown%20leveling%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20aspect%20of%20the%20plan%20is%20to%20down-level%20some%20of%20the%20managers%20to%20individual%20contributor%20roles%2C%20according%20to%20the%20recent%20guidelines%20for%20the%20AWS%20sales%20team.%20Two%20current%20AWS%20employees%20told%20BI%20that%20several%20managers%20have%20been%20pushed%20down%20a%20level%20due%20to%20the%20new%20approach.%20That%20meant%20being%20moved%20to%20a%20smaller%20pay%20band%2C%20one%20of%20the%20people%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20former%20employee%20who%20left%20recently%20said%20the%20promotion%20criteria%20are%20changing.%20This%20person%20said%20some%20AWS%20teams%20now%20require%20managers%20to%20have%20more%20people%20under%20them%20to%20qualify%20for%20a%20promotion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon's%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20moving%20from%20an%20individual%20contributor%20to%20a%20manager%20role%2C%20or%20vice%20versa%2C%20can%20happen%20without%20changing%20levels.%20There's%20no%20companywide%20requirement%20for%20team%20size%20to%20get%20promoted%20as%20the%20promotion%20criteria%20involve%20many%20factors%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20several%20Amazon%20employees%20who%20spoke%20to%20BI%2C%20the%20reorganization%20is%20creating%20a%20bigger%20problem%3A%20a%20culture%20of%20fear.%20They%20said%20managers%20seem%20to%20shy%20away%20from%20taking%20risks%20or%20making%20hard%20decisions%20because%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20held%20accountable%20for%20failures%2C%20which%20could%20make%20them%20a%20target%20of%20the%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20wants%20to%20be%20the%20one%20that%20failed%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20the%20people%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20at%20Amazon%3F%20Got%20a%20tip%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EContact%20the%20reporter%20Eugene%20Kim%20via%20the%20encrypted-messaging%20apps%20Signal%20or%20Telegram%20(%2B1-650-942-3061)%20or%20email%20(%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aekim%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eekim%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E).%20Reach%20out%20using%20a%20nonwork%20device.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ECheck%20out%20In