C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67994a28eb4be2fff9a2a91b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20certain%20level%20of%20zen%20that%20comes%20with%20boarding%20an%20airplane.%20The%20free-for-all%20may%20be%20stressful%2C%20but%20the%20chaos%20is%20also%20predictable.%20If%20you%20fly%20often%20enough%2C%20you%20can%20see%20from%20a%20mile%20away%20how%20the%20process%20is%20going%20to%20go%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20battle%20of%20the%20bags.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20typically%20starts%20with%20an%20unenthused%20agent%20issuing%20what%20seems%20like%20a%20far-too-early%20warning%20that%20overhead%20bin%20space%20is%20running%20out%2C%20causing%20a%20swarm%20of%20anxious%20passengers%20to%20crowd%20the%20gate%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20ensure%20their%20bag%20travels%20with%20them.%20Some%20passengers%20voluntarily%20hand%20over%20their%20luggage%20for%20a%20gate%20check%2C%20begrudgingly%20strapping%20on%20that%20dreaded%20red%20tag%2C%20while%20others%20hold%20out%2C%20betting%20that%20there's%20more%20room%20on%20the%20plane%20than%20the%20staff%20is%20letting%20on.%20If%20they're%20right%20and%20they%20make%20it%20past%20the%20gate%20agent%2C%20all's%20well%20that%20ends%20well.%20For%20those%20that%20play%20it%20wrong%2C%20well%2C%20they're%20in%20for%20a%20kerfuffle%20%E2%80%94%20the%20last-ditch%20attempt%20to%20squeeze%20the%20bag%20in%2C%20the%20plea%20with%20a%20flight%20attendant%20to%20come%20up%20with%20a%20fix%2C%20and%2C%20ultimately%2C%20the%20decision%20to%20relent.%20The%20flight%20eventually%20takes%20off%2C%20often%20delayed%2C%20with%20everyone%20slightly%20more%20annoyed%20than%20they%20were%2030%20minutes%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hubbub%20around%20luggage%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bsingle%20driver%20of%20boarding%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Samuel%20Engel%2C%20a%20lecturer%20at%20Boston%20University's%20Questrom%20School%20of%20Business%20and%20a%20senior%20vice%20president%20at%20ICF%2C%20a%20consulting%20firm.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20what%20is%20the%20constraint%20on%20boarding%20time%2C%20the%20element%20that%20really%20squeezes%20it%20is%20the%20overhead%20bins.%20It's%20not%20people%20finding%20their%20seats.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20how%20recurrent%20this%20problem%20is%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20someone%20should%20have%20fixed%20it%20by%20now.%20But%20instead%2C%20the%20handling%20of%20carry-on%20luggage%20has%20become%20an%20inevitable%20pain%20point%20in%20flying.%20The%20airlines%20have%20made%20checking%20bags%20an%20unappealing%20proposition%2C%20given%20the%20cost%20and%20the%20risk%20of%20items%20being%20mishandled%2C%20meaning%20more%20people%20are%20trying%20to%20cram%20their%20possessions%20into%20increasingly%20packed%20planes.%20And%20while%20carriers%20try%20to%20squeeze%20every%20last%20dollar%20out%20of%20baggage%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20us%20are%20pitted%20against%20each%20other%20%E2%80%94%20passenger%20versus%20passenger%2C%20staff%20versus%20passenger%2C%20lenient%20gate%20agents%20versus%20strict%20flight%20attendants%20%E2%80%94%20which%20makes%20the%20flying%20experience%20just%20a%20little%20more%20miserable.%20Passengers%20have%20to%20take%20a%20%26quot%3BJesus%20take%20the%20roller-bag%20wheels%26quot%3B%20approach%20to%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20flying%20nowadays.%20The%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20handled%2016.4%20million%20flights%20in%20fiscal%202023%2C%20with%20an%20average%20of%202.9%20million%20passengers%20flying%20in%20and%20out%20of%20US%20airports%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlanes%20are%20more%20crowded%2C%20too.%20The%20annual%20load%20factor%2C%20meaning%20the%20percentage%20of%20seats%20actually%20filled%20by%20a%20passenger%2C%20is%20over%2080%25.%20Department%20of%20Transportation%20data%20provided%20by%20Airlines%20for%20America%2C%20which%20represents%20major%20airlines%20in%20the%20US%2C%20indicates%20that%20on%20the%20average%20domestic%20US%20flight%20there%20are%20106%20passengers%20and%20130%20seats%3B%20that's%20a%20big%20jump%20from%20an%20average%20of%2065%20passengers%20and%2092%20seats%20in%202004.%20For%20international%20flights%20into%20and%20out%20of%20the%20US%2C%20there%20are%20158%20passengers%20and%20194%20seats%2C%20compared%20with%20just%20111%20passengers%20and%20151%20seats%2020%20years%20ago.%20Some%20of%20the%20increase%20is%20a%20result%20of%20bigger%20planes%2C%20but%20they're%20more%20packed%2C%20too.%20Engel%20said%20the%20American%20Airlines%20Boeing%20737-800%2C%20for%20example%2C%20had%20148%20total%20seats%20upon%20delivery%20in%202000.%20By%202013%2C%20that%20number%20was%20160.%20In%202024%2C%20it%20was%20172.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20take%20a%20look%20at%20the%20same%20airplane%2010%20years%20ago%20today%2C%20it%20has%20more%20seats%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bob%20Mann%2C%20an%20aviation%20analyst.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20percentage%20of%20seats%20occupied%20on%20average%2010%20years%20ago%20versus%20today%2C%20that%20percentage%20is%20higher.%20So%20more%20seats%20and%20a%20higher%20percentage%20occupied%20definitely%20means%20more%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20people%20on%20a%20plane%20translates%20to%20more%20money%20for%20carriers.%20It%20reduces%20their%20cost%20per%20available%20seat%20mile%2C%20increasing%20efficiency%20and%20profitability.%20So%20airlines%20have%20reduced%20the%20sizes%20of%20bathrooms%20and%20galleys%20and%20even%20the%20space%20between%20seats%20to%20squeeze%20more%20flyers%20in%2C%20all%20in%20the%20name%20of%20maximizing%20the%20number%20of%20paying%20customers%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20average%20aircraft%20density%20is%20up%20substantially%2C%26quot%3B%20Engel%20said.%20%26quot%3BEven%20on%20the%20same%20plane%2C%20there's%20just%20more%20seats%20on%20the%20plane%20than%20there%20used%20to%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20passengers%2C%20of%20course%2C%20aren't%20flying%20empty-handed.%20They've%20got%20luggage%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20are%20trying%20to%20bring%20that%20luggage%20on%20board.%20The%20carry-on-bag%20problem%20is%20partly%20related%20to%20space%20and%20partly%20to%20economics.%20There%20often%20isn't%20enough%20room%20on%20planes%20to%20fit%20everyone's%20bags%2C%20because%20the%20planes%20weren't%20designed%20to%20handle%20them%20all%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20That's%20especially%20true%20as%20planes%20become%20more%20crowded%20and%20the%20mix%20of%20people%20flying%20leans%20more%20toward%20leisure%20than%20business.%20(You%20pack%20more%20for%20vacation%20than%20you%20do%20for%20a%20one-day%20business%20meeting.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20all%20this%2C%20the%20incentives%20around%20bags%20are%20wacky%20%E2%80%94%20airlines%20have%20made%20checking%20a%20bag%20so%20undesirable%20that%20more%20people%20try%20to%20carry%20theirs%20on.%20The%20spark%20of%20the%20carry-on-bag%20conundrum%20dates%20back%20to%202008%2C%20when%20American%20Airlines%20became%20the%20first%20major%20US%20airline%20to%20start%20charging%20passengers%20to%20check%20a%20bag%2C%20thanks%20in%20part%20to%20skyrocketing%20oil%20prices.%20It%20was%20followed%20quickly%20by%20United%20Airlines.%20Sure%2C%20the%20budget%20carriers%20had%20done%20it%20first%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20big%20deal%20for%20the%20big%20guys%20to%20start%20charging%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJet%20fuel%20was%20increasing%20dramatically%2C%20and%20airlines%20were%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20cover%20those%20higher%20costs%20without%20having%20to%20hike%20airfares%2C%20because%20they%20knew%20that%20if%20they%20raised%20airfares%20too%20much%20it%20would%20further%20dampen%20demand%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Henry%20Harteveldt%2C%20the%20president%20of%20Atmosphere%20Research%20Group%2C%20a%20travel%20industry%20consulting%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20proliferation%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairlines-made-estimated-33-billion-from-baggage-fees-last-year-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efees%20across%20the%20airline%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Today%2C%20charges%20for%20checking%20bags%20and%20choosing%20seats%20are%20among%20the%20largest%20ancillary%20revenue%20generators%20for%20airlines.%20They%20make%20billions%20of%20dollars%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fairline-baggage-fees%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echecked-bag%20fees%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20year.%20But%20not%20every%20passenger%20is%20eager%20to%20hand%20over%20%2450%20to%20not%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20their%20suitcase%20until%20they%20reach%20their%20destination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20extremely%20price%20sensitive%20or%20on%20a%20very%20tight%20budget%2C%20or%20if%20you%20are%20a%20family%20traveling%2C%20all%20of%20that%2C%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20a%20checked%20bag%2C%26quot%3B%20Harteveldt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20ways%20to%20avoid%20the%20fee%20if%20you%20have%20airline%20status%20or%20a%20special%20credit%20card%2C%20though%20many%20travelers%20aren't%20so%20fortunate.%20Beyond%20that%2C%20there%20are%20other%20reasons%20people%20aren't%20so%20jazzed%20about%20the%20idea%20of%20checking%20their%20bags.%20They%20don't%20want%20to%20wait%20to%20pick%20it%20up%20after%20the%20flight%2C%20they've%20got%20stuff%20in%20it%20they%20want%20to%20use%20midflight%2C%20and%2C%20perhaps%20most%20importantly%2C%20they%20don't%20trust%20the%20airline%20to%20get%20the%20bag%20to%20their%20destination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20bags%20you%20handle%2C%20the%20more%20bags%20you%20lose.%20That's%20just%20math%2C%26quot%3B%20Mann%20said.%20The%20airlines'%20economic%20motivations%20for%20charging%20for%20checked%20bags%20were%20understandable%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20the%20real%20end-to-end%20consequences%20were%20not%20understood.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20this%20all%20adds%20up%20to%20is%20a%20persistent%20crisis%20at%20the%20gate.%20Smaller%20planes%20especially%20don't%20have%20enough%20space%20for%20everyone%20to%20store%20their%20bags%20in%20the%20overhead%20bins.%20There%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20dreaded%20bin%20hogs%20%E2%80%94%20the%20guy%20who%20ignores%20the%20one-overhead-item-per-person%20rule%20and%20takes%20up%20an%20entire%20bin%20with%20his%20roller%20bag%20and%20backpack%20and%20giant%20coat%20while%20leaving%20his%20fellow%20passengers%20to%20duke%20it%20out%20over%20dwindling%20space.%20A%20flight%20attendant%20could%20argue%20with%20him%20(and%20sometimes%20does)%2C%20but%20the%20ensuing%20battle%20holds%20boarding%20up%20more.%20Other%20small%20issues%20can%20add%20up%20to%20a%20large%20backup%2C%20such%20as%20flight%20attendants%20taking%20up%20some%20bin%20space%20for%20their%20own%20bags%20or%20passengers%20using%20less-than-perfect%20tactics%20to%20get%20their%20luggage%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20load%20the%20bags%20the%20optimal%20way%20either%2C%20so%20we're%20not%20actually%20maximizing%20the%20available%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gary%20Leff%2C%20who%20writes%20at%20View%20from%20the%20Wing%2C%20a%20website%20dedicated%20to%20flying%20and%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGate%20agents%20are%20increasingly%20stretched%20thin%20and%20under%20pressure%20%E2%80%94%20their%20primary%20objective%20is%20to%20get%20the%20flight%20to%20depart%20the%20gate%20on%20time%2C%20and%20if%20there%20are%20too%20many%20delays%20they%20get%20dinged.%20So%20to%20avoid%20the%20bag%20drama%20on%20the%20plane%2C%20they%20start%20asking%20for%20people%20to%20gate%20check%20their%20bags%20almost%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20flight%20starts%20boarding.%20The%20result%3A%20angry%20passengers%2C%20not%20only%20because%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20check%20their%20bags%20but%20also%20because%20if%20they%20do%20relent%2C%20they%20often%20get%20on%20the%20flight%20and%20see%20there's%20plenty%20of%20space%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGate%20agents%20aren't%20checking%20in%20with%20crew%20in%20real%20time%20over%20when%20bin%20space%20is%20actually%20full.%20And%20even%20if%20they%20did%2C%20that%20wouldn't%20give%20them%20the%20information%20they%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20Leff%20said.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20all%2C%20full%20bins%20with%20passengers%20still%20on%20the%20jetbridge%20with%20carry-on%20bags%20would%20still%20mean%20having%20to%20bring%20bags%20off%20the%20aircraft%20to%20be%20gate%20checked.%20So%20gate%20agents%20require%20it%20long%20before%20overhead%20bins%20actually%20fill%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20passengers%2C%20this%20can%20seem%20unfair%20and%20arbitrary.%20People%20can%20feel%20like%20they're%20being%20picked%20on%20by%20staffers%20who%20seem%20to%20select%20them%20at%20random%20to%20check%20their%20bags%20while%20others%20breeze%20by.%20Perhaps%20they're%20asked%20to%20fit%20their%20bag%20into%20a%20sizer%20that%20supposedly%20lines%20up%20with%20the%20bins%20on%20the%20plane%2C%20but%20they're%20convinced%20it's%20too%20small%20and%20not%20representative%20of%20the%20real%20thing.%20Or%20they've%20been%20sold%20luggage%20that's%20marketed%20as%20fitting%20the%20carry-on%20standard%2C%20only%20to%20discover%20that%20airline%20standards%20can%20vary%20or%20that%20their%20bag%20is%20on%20the%20larger%20side%20for%20the%20carrier%20they%20picked%20for%20that%20trip.%20Leff%20said%20bag%20sizers%20at%20gates%20are%20usually%20slightly%20larger%20than%20the%20published%20dimensions%20of%20what's%20allowed%20on%20the%20plane%2C%20but%20he%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bmany%20carry-on%20bags%20are%20larger%20than%20the%20sizes%20they're%20advertised%20at.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20worth%20mentioning%20that%2C%20as%20easy%20as%20it%20is%20to%20complain%20about%20US%20airlines%2C%20they%20are%20often%20more%20forgiving%20about%20luggage%20than%20foreign%20carriers.%20Generally%2C%20when%20European%20airlines%20tell%20you%20how%20much%20your%20carry-on%20can%20weigh%2C%20they%20mean%20it.%20US%20carriers%20can%20be%20a%20bit%20more%20random%20on%20the%20rules%2C%20which%20may%20or%20may%20not%20work%20out%20to%20a%20passenger's%20benefit.%20Also%2C%20I'm%20not%20addressing%20the%20issue%20of%20paid%20carry-ons%20here%2C%20which%20we'll%20leave%20for%20another%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20asked%20aviation%20analysts%20and%20consultants%20about%20solutions%20to%20the%20carry-on-bag%20dilemma%2C%20their%20responses%20were%20not%20super%20optimistic.%20On%20a%20positive%20note%2C%20airlines%20are%20adding%20bigger%20bins%20%E2%80%94%20United%20and%20Alaska%20have%20announced%20plans%20to%20increase%20bin%20space%2C%20which%20in%20theory%20should%20mean%20every%20passenger%20can%20bring%20on%20and%20store%20a%20standard%20roll-aboard%20suitcase.%20These%20tweaks%20won't%20address%20the%20aforementioned%20bin%20hogs%2C%20though.%20On%20a%20negative%20note%2C%20one%20of%20the%20main%20drivers%20of%20the%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20more%20and%20more%20passengers%20being%20fit%20onto%20planes%20%E2%80%94%20is%20not%20going%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAirlines%20are%20doing%20everything%20they%20can%20to%20cram%20as%20many%20seats%20on%20a%20plane%20to%20make%20as%20much%20money%20as%20they%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20Harteveldt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirlines%20could%20do%20more%20to%20get%20passengers%20to%20check%20their%20bags.%20Leff%20said%20Southwest%2C%20which%20allows%20for%20two%20free%20checked%20bags%2C%20avoids%20the%20carry-on%20drama%20more%20than%20other%20airlines.%20Other%20airlines%20could%20follow%20suit%2C%20though%20they%20may%20not%20be%20eager%20to%20give%20up%20that%20baggage-fee%20cash%20cow.%20Charges%20aside%2C%20if%20airlines%20were%20better%20at%20getting%20bags%20out%20faster%20%E2%80%94%20and%20reassuring%20passengers%20that%20their%20bags%20won't%20be%20lost%20%E2%80%94%20that%20might%20inspire%20some%20more%20checking%2C%20too.%20Some%20carriers%20are%20trying%20to%20put%20passengers'%20minds%20at%20ease%20by%20making%20it%20possible%20for%20them%20to%20track%20their%20bags%20as%20they%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20we're%20doomed%20to%20perpetually%20experience%20some%20level%20of%20chaos%20over%20baggage%20at%20the%20gate.%20So%20I%20asked%20the%20various%20aviation%20gurus%20I%20spoke%20with%20for%20their%20own%20approaches%20to%20carry-on%20luggage%20and%20for%20any%20tips%20or%20tricks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEngel%20told%20me%20he%20packs%20light%20and%20gets%20on%20early.%20If%20he%20can%20get%20into%20an%20exit%20row%2C%20even%20better%2C%20because%20there%20are%20fewer%20seats%20and%20therefore%20more%20bin%20space.%20Leff%20employs%20a%20similar%20strategy%2C%20though%20he%20admitted%20that%20on%20one%20occasion%20he%20cheated%20the%20system.%20An%20agent%20asked%20him%20to%20tag%20his%20bag%20for%20gate%20check%20and%20leave%20it%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20jetbridge.%20He%20complied%20with%20the%20tagging%2C%20but%20he%20took%20the%20bag%20on%20the%20plane%20anyway.%20He%20acknowledged%20it%20would%20have%20been%20a%20problem%20if%20everyone%20did%20it%2C%20but%20they%20didn't%2C%20and%20the%20flight%20was%20already%20delayed%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarteveldt%20said%20sometimes%20he%20finds%20it's%20worth%20it%20just%20to%20pay%20to%20check%20the%20bag%20to%20avoid%20the%20bin-space%20stress.%20I%20confessed%20my%20personal%20workaround%20to%20him%3A%20I%20ask%20to%20check%20my%20bag%20the%20minute%20I%20get%20to%20the%20gate%2C%20regardless%20of%20whether%20it's%20been%20requested.%20The%20gate%20agent%20almost%20always%20says%20yes%2C%20and%20I%20get%20to%20skip%20the%20checked-bag%20fee.%20Harteveldt%20told%20me%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bwell-known%20hack%26quot%3B%20and%20described%20another%20%26quot%3Bdirty%20little%20secret%26quot%3B%20I%20might%20want%20to%20use%20to%20adjust%20my%20approach%3A%20If%20you%20check%20your%20bag%20at%20the%20last%20minute%2C%20it's%20loaded%20at%20the%20last%20minute%2C%20meaning%20it%20has%20a%20better%20chance%20of%20being%20the%20first%20off%20the%20plane.%20%26quot%3BNot%20always%2C%20it's%20not%20guaranteed%2C%20but%20sometimes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20that%20the%20battle%20of%20the%20bags%20is%20here%20to%20stay.%20Passengers%20may%20not%20win%20the%20war%2C%20but%20they%20can%20at%20least%20come%20armed%20with%20a%20couple%20of%20tactics%20for%20the%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarry-on-bags-checked-luggage-size-charge-airlines-planes-travel-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738228021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67994a48eb4be2fff9a2a923%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarry-on-bags-checked-luggage-size-charge-airlines-planes-travel-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Carry-on%20luggage%20is%20causing%20big%20headaches%20for%20travelers%2C%20gate%20agents%2C%20and%20flight%20attendants.%20It%20also%20helps%20airlines%20rake%20in%20big-time%20cash.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A60%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarry-on-bags-checked-luggage-size-charge-airlines-planes-travel-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22ti